Module kivakit.data.compression
Package com.telenav.kivakit.data.compression

Interface SymbolConsumer<Symbol>

Functional Interface:
This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.
@FunctionalInterface public interface SymbolConsumer<Symbol>
Consumer of a sequence of decoded symbols. The next(int, Object) method is called with each decoded symbol and its ordinal index in the input. The next() method can examine the symbol and return a SymbolConsumer.Directive to the codec to either SymbolConsumer.Directive.CONTINUE decoding or to SymbolConsumer.Directive.STOP. When the codec reads an escape symbol, it will advance the input to the next byte and call the onEscape(ByteList) method to permit it to read the next symbol using the coding scheme implemented in SymbolProducer.
